  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Open Contracting for Health (OC4H)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transparency International&#x2019;s Pharmaceuticals and Healthcare Programme (TI PHP), together with the Open Contracting Partnership and the World Health Organization, and with financial support from the UK Department for International Development (DfID), will serve to facilitate the implementation of open contracting in the health sector in key priority countries in Sub Saharan Africa and Asia as a way to curb corruption and ensure better use of scarce public funds for health. This will entail a strong alliance with national governments, medical product and service providers and civil society organisations that together establish the so-called &#x201C;golden triangle&#x201D; needed for effective open contracting.</narrative>
  </description>
